## This session: author a new CARRIER BOARD

You are authoring a new carrier-board catalogue entry under
`catalogue/boards/<arch>-<chip>-<carrier>/`.

## Read these FIRST, in this order

1. `specifications/SPEC-CATALOGUE-LAYOUT.md` ¬ß3 ‚Äî **the normative
   board-authoring spec**. The full RFC 2119 schema for `board.toml`,
   the canonical BOARD.md + AI-CONTEXT.md section structures, the
   `templates/` file inventory, the ¬ß3.3.9 validation rules.

2. `specifications/SPEC-APIARY-FLASH.md` ¬ß4.1 ‚Äî the REQUIRED `[usb]`
   table that every MCU board.toml carries.

3. The canonical example: `catalogue/boards/esp32-c6-dfr1117/`. Read
   `board.toml` (full schema including `[pinout.*]`, `[capabilities]`,
   `[references]`, `[compulsory_plugins]`, `[notes]`); `BOARD.md`
   (8 required H2 sections); `AI-CONTEXT.md` (10 required H2 sections);
   `templates/` (full inventory).

4. Upstream R2 references cited by ¬ß3:
   - R2-COMPILE ¬ß4 (platform tags: `esp32`, `nrf`, `rp2`, `avr`,
     `linux-embedded`).
   - R2-BUILD ¬ß2 (target triples table).
   - R2-HW (multi-processor, pin remapping, USB topology).

## What you MUST produce

Per SPEC-CATALOGUE-LAYOUT ¬ß3.1:

- `catalogue/boards/<slug>/board.toml` ‚Äî full schema per ¬ß3.3.
- `catalogue/boards/<slug>/BOARD.md` ‚Äî 8 H2 sections in fixed order
  (At a glance / Role in r2-composer / Where to wire what / Build & flash
  / Templates / Known gotchas / Authoring history / See also).
- `catalogue/boards/<slug>/AI-CONTEXT.md` ‚Äî 10 H2 sections in fixed
  order per ¬ß3.5.
- `catalogue/boards/<slug>/datasheets/HARDWARE-WIRING-<UPPER>.md` ‚Äî
  the wiring guide referenced by `[references].wiring_guide`.
- `catalogue/boards/<slug>/templates/` ‚Äî `Cargo.toml.tera`, `.cargo/config.toml`,
  `build.rs`, `rust-toolchain.toml`. ESP-IDF carriers additionally need
  `sdkconfig.defaults` + `partitions.csv`. WiFi-capable carriers also
  `wifi_config.toml.example`.
- `catalogue/boards/<slug>/conversation/<date>-author-board-NN.md` ‚Äî transcript.

## Constraints

- Directory name: `<arch>-<chip>-<carrier>`, kebab-case (per ¬ß3.1).
- `[board].name` MUST equal the directory name.
- Class string is implicit: `ai.reality2.board.<carrier>` ‚Äî DO NOT
  hard-code its hash in board.toml (¬ß3.2).
- `[build].target_triple` MUST appear in R2-BUILD ¬ß2.
- `[compile_target].tag` MUST appear in R2-DEF ¬ß7.7 (or be a new tag
  you're claiming ‚Äî flag this case in `[notes].gotchas` and surface it
  to the operator before committing).
- `[compulsory_plugins].capabilities` MUST contain
  `"ai.reality2.deploy.ota"` (SPEC-CATALOGUE-LAYOUT ¬ß3.3.7).
- For ESP carriers: `[usb]` table per SPEC-APIARY-FLASH ¬ß4.1 with the
  correct VID/PID, `chip_id_probe`, `esptool_chip_arg`,
  `reset_strategy`, `flash_offsets`. The disambiguator matters ‚Äî
  ESP32-S3 and ESP32-C6 both report VID 0x303a PID 0x1001 for native
  USB-Serial-JTAG.

## How to ask clarifying questions

Per the calm-computing posture: short questions, one fact at a time.
Confirm vendor URL, chip family, USB topology, available peripherals,
flash size, PSRAM presence before generating `board.toml`. WebFetch the
vendor's page if the operator gave you a URL. If they gave you a PDF
path, Read it.

